race.comment: ARTISSI (8) was denied narrowly first-up but went right on with the job last time to score comfortably at Mt Gambier. Has more to offer third-up, though is likely to drift back from the draw. BELLENTIA (10) is yet to strike through this campaign but is knocking on the door. Will appreciate the drop in grade and is drawn favourably. No shock to see her in the finish. DEFICIT (2) was a barnstorming winner two back at long odds but less effective last time. Tough to assess but is worth some thought on his peaks. FROSTY NIGHT (9) continues to finish thereabouts. Has good tactical speed and gets in well with the claim. Have to consider. HASTA LA CHILLY (3) can improve sharply second-up on his home track. Don't dismiss.
